item.title: Any oldfags around?
item.dc:creator: @Tree Tree
item.description:
@Tree wrote:

[quote=“Ruby, post:122, topic:523159”][quote author=Tree link=topic=641709.msg4322810#msg4322810 date=1372429055]
The joining date doesn’t always show the real story. For example, I’ve been around the scene for a long time and was relatively late to join this particular site. As well as this, Tree wasn’t my initial alias.

Generally, the long term members have contributed more and have experienced the scene at it’s peak (fkers stripped my awards). The age of exploration I guess. I do believe that the success of a new community relies on there being one or two ‘veteran’ individuals from previous communities. For example, some of the mods from Kaitnieks help build a nice foundation for mitb.

It’s been the trend for a while. RSCN, RuneCMS, Sythe, free games forums, Villvavu, ecg, Kaitnieks, rsresources and Impsoft. The leading members of those forums were the respected members from the previous. A legacy. Now though, there’s very few of us left.
[/quote]
Just because there’s very few of the original members left doesn’t mean that a lot of them haven’t passed on knowledge of the history to the newer members (like the thread you recently posted) who will undoubtedly continue the legacy throughout communities when this closes. Look at Villavu, that’s still going incredibly strong all these years on and their irc channel on rizon is one of the busiest channels on the network.[/quote]

It’s cold tonight. I’m shirtless and I can’t help but notice I’m slowly putting on weight. Not that I’m overweight. In fact, I’d consider myself fairly average on the old scales. Perhaps I should set up a bench press in my shed or something. I do have a plank of wood and two buckets laying around from when I cut an old table in half. It was taking up way too much room and my fish tank needed somewhere to stand.

I have a few animals. My favorite is an old stray that we found. It wasn’t vicious at all and hugely affectionate. It’s next to me now, also struggling with the freezing temperature. The problem with cats is they always leave a trail of hair wherever they go. There’s nothing worse than accidentally rolling on to her spot and copping a mouthful of fur. That’s love I guess.

Either way, Villavu still has a solid base of old members so that argument doesn’t really count. You’re right with the history side of things. Yes, it’s passed on like my thread posted earlier. This doesn’t mean the actual technical knowledge is passed on. The original key developers keep a lot to themselves and a lot has been lost over the years. That’s how I view it anyway. I’m just a washed up old Tree.

My Cat Playing Counter-Strike (headshots galore):

Washed Up Old Tree (the female is silab. she’s naked):

EDIT: Increased breast size. Lowered brain settings.
